 Career History



Co-Founder

                                    2014 - Current                


NodeSource, Inc.


                  NodeSource, Inc. operates software company created to build a robust product ecosystem. It is a technology company dedicated to delivering enterprise-grade software products in support of a sustainable ecosystem for the open source Node project. The company was founded by Dan Shaw and Joe McCann in 2014 and is headquartered in New York, NY.                





 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ‚ñæ




Member, Advisory Board

                    2016 - Current                  


Localeur LLC

                    Localeur is a community of locals who share recommendations on their favorite places to eat, drink and play to help travelers experience local in their cities. Unlike review sites like Yelp, Localeur has an exclusive community of local insiders who share authentic recommendations on places in the cities they live in, not the ones they visit.

Launched before SXSW 2013, Localeur was dubbed one of the top mobile apps of SXSW by Digital Trends and an "A-Lister" by SXSW and the Greater Austin Chamber of Commerce. Austin Monthly deemed Localeur the "Best New Startup" for 2013.

"Hoping to follow in the steps of established travel review sites such as TripAdvisor and Yelp, Localeur a new travel startup launched...The site will focus on the needs of Millennial travelers by using local recommendations from a selected community of local insiders." - Black Enterprise

"By focusing on truly local people who have profiles and can develop their own mystique/cult-of-personality, the company ensures a more emotional, direct connection that can parlay into traction across cities as they grow." - Tnooz

"There is a terrific mix of tips for foodies, nature-lovers, culture-seekers and more." - LA Times

"Be sure to download Localeur, which offers locals' opinions on everything--what to eat, shop, do, see, etc. It's a great way to even discover your own city." - Huffington Post

"Make sure to bookmark Localeur and impress your friends with inside information on the hottest local attractions." - Examiner, NY

"Unlike the online rating site Yelp.com, Localeur doesn't review destinations, and its guides tend to steer travelers away from places that locals consider overrated." - Denver Post

"Much like modern dating, eating out has become staggering array of choice. Smartphone apps like Ness or Localeur make finding a restaurant easier than a date." - TIME                  




